Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer
The Dodgers scored three more runs in the seventh to beat the Padres 7-2
Post-Match Reflections: The Dodgers had not clinched at home since the pandemic-shortened 2020 season
A sellout crowd of 52,433, including retired Dodgers star Manny Ramirez, packed Dodger Stadium for the finale of the crucial series between the top teams in the NL West
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers had already clinched a postseason berth
Freddie Freeman left the game after awkwardly colliding with Luis Arráez and the first base bag trying to avoid being tagged for the second out of the seventh inning
Others: The Padres led 2-0 as Joe Musgrove pitched six shutout innings

Evan Phillips replaced Buehler in the sixth and gave up back-to-back singles to Jurickson Profar and Machado. They moved up on Jackson Merrill’s sacrifice bunt. Profar scored on Xander Bogaerts’ sacrifice fly to center for a 2-0 lead
